chassisHWRev.name: chassisHWRev
chassisHWRev.description: The chassis hardware revision. For non-TNT platforms it is always reported as empty string.

chassisRedundancy.name: chassisRedundancy
chassisRedundancy.description: Value to indicate if this platform is running with redundant controller.

chassisMemTotal.name: chassisMemTotal
chassisMemTotal.description: The total RAM (bytes) on the shelf controller.

chassisMemAvail.name: chassisMemAvail
chassisMemAvail.description: The RAM (bytes) currently available on the shelf controller.

chassisMemThreshold.name: chassisMemThreshold
chassisMemThreshold.description: The low water mark for RAM (bytes) on the shelf controller.

cntrReduSwitchLastTime.name: cntrReduSwitchLastTime
cntrReduSwitchLastTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the controller switched over, 0 if none after last system reboot.

cntrReduSwitchReason.name: cntrReduSwitchReason
cntrReduSwitchReason.description: Reason for last controller switchover, unknown if no switchover has occurred.

cntrReduSwitchIndex.name: cntrReduSwitchIndex
cntrReduSwitchIndex.description: Controller Index into slot-table for last controller that was switched from.

cntrReduAvailLastTime.name: cntrReduAvailLastTime
cntrReduAvailLastTime.description: The last time the redundacy availabilty state changed. This object reports 0 if the system did not yet transition from the boot stage.

cntrReduAvailPrevState.name: cntrReduAvailPrevState
cntrReduAvailPrevState.description: The previous redundancy state. It's value is other before the first transition.

cntrReduAvailCurrState.name: cntrReduAvailCurrState
cntrReduAvailCurrState.description: The current redundancy state. It's value is boot before the first transition.

cntrReduAvailSlotIndex.name: cntrReduAvailSlotIndex
cntrReduAvailSlotIndex.description: The slotIndex as used in the slot table for the slot that observed the transition.

slotNumber.name: slotNumber
slotNumber.description: The number of slots, fixed or removable, supported by this device.

slotTable.name: slotTable
slotTable.description: A list of slot entries. The number of entries is given by the value slotNumber.

slotEntry.name: slotEntry
slotEntry.description: A slot entry containing objects to describe the slot.

slotIndex.name: slotIndex
slotIndex.description: A unique value for each slot card. Its value ranges between 1 and the value slotNumber.

slotName.name: slotName
slotName.description: The ASCII representation of the name of the card in the indexed slot. The name is the same name displayed on the Main Edit Menu less the menu number. The empty string is returned when there is no slot card present. The value 'Not Avail' is used when the card in the slot has failed POST. The value 'Occupied' is used for cards occupying more than one slot space.

slotType.name: slotType
slotType.description: The type of card in the indexed slot.

slotFixed.name: slotFixed
slotFixed.description: The value fixed( 1 ) returned if the slot card is not removable and removable( 2 ) if the slot card is removable.

slotItems.name: slotItems
slotItems.description: A count of the number of 'items' contained by this slot card. An 'item' is a 'port' for host and a 'line' for network slot cards.

slotSpecific.name: slotSpecific
slotSpecific.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the hardware in this slot card. Contains the object identifier { 0 0 } if there is no slot specific information for the current slot card type.

slotSerialNumber.name: slotSerialNumber
slotSerialNumber.description: The TNT slot card's serial number. The serial number is reported as 0 if the slot card does not have a serial number, if the card did not boot, or if the slot is empty. The serial number is reported as 7777777 if the slot card does not support serialization. The serial number is reported as 0 for platforms other than TNT.

slotStatus.name: slotStatus
slotStatus.description: The current status of the TNT slot card For non-TNT systems operStateNone is always reported.

slotLastChange.name: slotLastChange
slotLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the TNT slot card entered its current state. For non-TNT systems 0 is always reported.

slotHWRev.name: slotHWRev
slotHWRev.description: Hardware revision of the slot card. On systems that do not support this object, an empty string is returned.

slotSWRev.name: slotSWRev
slotSWRev.description: Software revision of the slot card. On systems that do not support this object, an empty string is returned.

slotAdminStatus.name: slotAdminStatus
slotAdminStatus.description: This attribute changes the state of the slot card or deletes the slot card. When read, returns the last admin. state set. For non-TNT systems slotAdminStatusUp(1) always returned. For non-TNT system this attribute can not be SET and GENERAL_ERROR(5) is returned, if a SET-REQUEST is received.

slotUpTime.name: slotUpTime
slotUpTime.description: Time the slot card has been up. If the slot card is not UP, returns 0.

slotMemoryTotal.name: slotMemoryTotal
slotMemoryTotal.description: Total RAM(bytes) present on the slot card.

slotMemoryAvail.name: slotMemoryAvail
slotMemoryAvail.description: The amount of RAM(bytes) currently available.

slotMemoryThreshold.name: slotMemoryThreshold
slotMemoryThreshold.description: The RAM low water mark (bytes) for the slot card.

slotItemTable.name: slotItemTable
slotItemTable.description: A list of slot item entries. Each slot contains slotItems entries, indexed by slotItemSlotIndex and by slotItemIndex

slotItemEntry.name: slotItemEntry
slotItemEntry.description: A slot entry containing the starting interface and number of interfaces used by the indexed slot/item.

slotItemSlotIndex.name: slotItemSlotIndex
slotItemSlotIndex.description: A unique value for each slot card. The slot card identified by a particular value of this index is the same slot card as identified by the same value of slotIndex.

slotItemIndex.name: slotItemIndex
slotItemIndex.description: A unique value for each item in each slot card. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of slotItems in the slot indexed by the same value as slotItemSlotIndex.

slotItemFirstIf.name: slotItemFirstIf
slotItemFirstIf.description: The interface number associated with the indexed item on the indexed slot. May be set to 0 if the slot/item is not associated with any interface.

slotItemIfCount.name: slotItemIfCount
slotItemIfCount.description: The number of interfaces associated with the indexed item on the indexed slot. Typically set to 1 for host slots and the number of channels on network (WAN) slots. May be set to 0 when the item is not associated with an interface.

slotItemSpecific.name: slotItemSpecific
slotItemSpecific.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the indexed item on the indexed slot. Contains the object identifier { 0 0 } if there is no item specific information for the indexed item.

slotItemStatus.name: slotItemStatus
slotItemStatus.description: The current status of this item in this slot card.

slotIfTable.name: slotIfTable
slotIfTable.description: A list of interfaces and the slot/item entry that the interface is associated with.

slotIfEntry.name: slotIfEntry
slotIfEntry.description: A slot interface entry containing the slot and item that the interface is associated with.

slotIfIndex.name: slotIfIndex
slotIfIndex.description: The interface index, ranging from 1 to the number of interfaces specified in the MIB-II variable ifNumber. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

slotIfSlotIndex.name: slotIfSlotIndex
slotIfSlotIndex.description: The slot index, ranging from 0 to the number of slots specified in slotNumber. When zero the interface references an item in the console group of this MIB. Otherwise the slot identified by a particular value of this index is the same slot as identified by the same value of slotIndex.

slotIfItemIndex.name: slotIfItemIndex
slotIfItemIndex.description: The item index, ranging from 1 to the number of items supported on the slot indicated by slotIfSlotIndex. When slotIfSlotIndex is non-zero the number of items supported is specified in slotItems for the slot entry index by slotIfSlotIndex. The item identified by a particular value of this index is the same item as identified by the same value of slotItemIndex.
